<TITLE> Faridpur road crash kills 4 including BNP leaders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com)--Four people, two of them local BNP leaders, were killed on Friday in a road accident near Maligram in Bhanga upazila, of Faridpur district. Co-convener of Faridpur district BNP Qazi Nazrul Islam, 50, co-convener of Bhanga upazila municipalilty's BNP unit and councillor of Bhanga municipality Tutul Munshi, 40, were among the dead. The rest were identified as 'Miraj', 30, from Rasulpur village and 'Hannan', 35, from Dangi, both in Nagarkanda upazila. Bhanga police chief Mohammed Marfat Ullah told bdnews24.com a bus headed for Dhaka collided with an oncoming car at around 3pm near Maligram on Dhaka-Khulna highway. Everyone in the private car died in the incident, he added. The car was going to Bhanga from Faridpur, the police officer said. Police had recovered the dead bodies, which had been sent to Bhanga Upazila Health Complex. The bus was seized but the driver and the conductor fled away, he added. bdnews24
